images.alt: a hulking, green-skinned orc, his corded muscles glistening under the flickering amber glow of lanterns hanging from the tavern’s smoke-stained rafters. His broad, tusked jaw is set in a smirk as he raises a frothy tankard of beer, the golden liquid sloshing dangerously close to the rim. Scars crisscross his thick forearms, hinting at countless brawls, and his leather vest strains against his barrel chest, barely containing the raw power beneath. Around him, the dimly lit barroom buzzes with low chatter and clinking glasses, shadows dancing across rough-hewn wooden tables where equally rugged patrons cast wary but respectful glances his way. Behind him, a broken axe leans against the bar—its handle splintered, its blade notched—yet the orc pays it no mind, lost in the simple pleasure of his drink, a rare moment of peace in a life carved from violence.
